The '''2014 [[Oddset Hockey Games]]''' is played between 1–4 May 2014. The [[Czech Republic men's national ice hockey team|Czech Republic]], [[Finland men's national ice hockey team|Finland]], [[Sweden men's national ice hockey team|Sweden]] and [[Russia men's national ice hockey team|Russia]] play a [[round-robin tournament|round-robin]] for a total of three games per team and six games in total. Five of the matches are played in the [[Ericsson Globe]] in [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]], and one match in the [[Hartwall Arena]] in [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]]. Finland won the tournament<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/hockey/landslag/article18823008.ab|title=Finland segerrikt inför VM-turnering|publisher=Sportbladet|language=English|date=4 May 2014|accessdate=2 February 2017}}</ref> for the fifth time. The tournament is a part of the [[2013–14 Euro Hockey Tour]].

